parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system when cold can cause the steering wheel to be difficult to turn, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Hard steering
difficulty turning the steering wheel
especially when the vehicle is cold
steering wheel and column lock-up
near accidents due to loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver Side Seat Belt Retractor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver side seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not retract properly, which can lead to reduced safety in the event of an accident, and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The driver side seat belt will not retract
the seat belt is stuck in an extended position
the seat belt cannot be pulled back into its retracted position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden and unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
the vehicle accelerates out of control
the vehicle fails to respond to braking input
the vehicle's speed increases unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to disengage
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle's speed increases without input from the driver
the vehicle fails to respond to braking input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drivetrain axle can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially even fires.
symptoms: Loud noise coming from the vehicle
drivetrain axle detached from the vehicle
transmission failure
fire under the vehicle.
